name: Lotte Fitin
description:
Sometimes as a photographer I feel limited to the type of creations I can come up with, as opposed to artists who draw their visions; however, I have been exploring different ways of making my aspirations into realities. 

In this image, I had my model friend pose for me in Dongdaemun Design Plaza. Dongdaemun is one of the largest shopping centers open 24 hours in Seoul. Lotte Fitin sits behind her, which is one of the shopping malls.

As she walked towards me, the lights flickered and danced behind her, creating a very surreal aura in the streets of the city. I've always imagined what the city could look like if buildings were a bit more crowded, I think the scene would look something like this.
